# Bug report

Starting with webpack 5.20.0 some of my generated module fail with an exception like this:
`TypeError: Cannot read property 'hy' of undefined`
when building in production mode but work in development mode.

By disabling the minimizer, I have been able to track the problem down to this line in the generated code:
`(0,types/* checkIsNonemptyString */.hy)(buttonName, 'buttonName');`
where `types` is an imported module and `checkIsNonemptyString` is the function to be invoked.
In the code generated by webpack 5.20.0 `types` is undefined and the code throws an exception.

**What is the current behavior?**

The generated fails when build with webpack > 5.20.0 in production mode but works works in development mode in all version and also works when build with webpack 5.19.0 in production mode.

**If the current behavior is a bug, please provide the steps to reproduce.**

This problem appeared in a very large project and it is very hard to reduce the complexity.
I'm currently unable to reproduce the problem in any reasonably sized example.
I very much hope, that the provided information at least helps to further track down the source of the problem.

